data.name: Wacker Chemie AG
data.description:
CREATING TOMORROW'S SOLUTIONS

As a pioneer of modern chemistry, today we are a globally active company with state-of-the-art specialty chemical products.

Our portfolio includes more than 3,200 products. You, our customers, come from virtually every major sector. We develop intelligent solutions and innovative technologies for you.

Customer-oriented and innovative with a long-term vision, we aim to improve people’s quality of life around the world.

WACKER has joined Race to Zero, the UN’s carbon neutrality initiative. We want to pursue specific projects and measures to halve our greenhouse gas emissions by 2030 and to ensure that how we work and make products achieves net-zero by 2045

data.name: ELASTOSIL® M
data.description: ELASTOSIL® M silicone rubber has been the ideal solution for the production of molds that are highly elastic and have excellent release properties and optimum durability. These invaluable processing properties make ELASTOSIL® M indispensable, to both industrial and artisan mold makers.

data.name: SILFAR
data.description: SILFAR® is the name of WACKER’s range of silicone-based products specifically intended for the pharmaceutical and food industries, as well as for use in fermentation and other biotech processes. SILFAR® products feature outstanding chemical resistance. They are not resorbed in the digestive tract, and are therefore not metabolized. They are colorless and odorless.

data.name: CAVAQ10
data.description: WACKER’s CAVAQ10® is a highly bioavailable coenzyme Q10 powder. This fat-soluble, vitamin-like substance is a known antioxidant. Coenzyme Q10 has been associated with improved cardiovascular health and supporting optimum fuctioning of the cardiac muscle. However, many commercial products do not offer adequate bioavailability. WACKER’s cyclodextrin-encapsulated CAVAQ10® powder, by contrast, has an 18-fold higher bioavailability compared to other CoQ10 products.

data.name: SILRES

properties.name: Product Families
items: Other Crop Protection & Pest Control Products

data.description: The SILRES® brand comprises a wide range of silicones for coatings, paints and construction applications. The portfolio has been developed and continuously improved since the 1950's when the first silicone resins for building protection originated in WACKER laboratories. It features not only time-tested and innovative products, but also tailored solutions for a host of applications, climates and substrates. And it is supported by a range of extensive services available from our technical centers worldwide which provide further customization and customer-specific options.

data.name: CAVAMAX
data.description: CAVAMAX® is the trade name for cyclodextrins from WACKER. We are the only company in the world to manufacture all three naturally occurring cyclodextrins – α, β and γ (CAVAMAX® W6, W7 and W8). CAVAMAX® cyclodextrins have unique properties resulting in a wide range of functionalities, such as stabilization, rheology control, masking of bitterness or increasing bioavailability and much more. This paves the way for innovative food, pharma and industrial applications.

data.name: VINNAPAS
data.description: VINNAPAS® is WACKER’s brand name for a versatile range of polymer-based dispersions, powders and resins that are used to improve the properties and performance of products in a wide range of industries. The portfolio has been continuously improved and optimized since the 1950s. Thus, VINNAPAS® products set the standard and are leading in many applications.

data.name: BELSIL

properties.name: INCI Name
items: Crotonic Acid/Vinyl C8-12 Isoalkyl Esters/VA/Bis-Vinyldimethicone Crosspolymer

data.description: BELSIL® is an extensive range of premium-grade silicones intended specifically for personal care applications, and more especially for hair care, skin care, color cosmetics, and deodorants. BELSIL® products are developed and manufactured in the highest quality and with utmost care, ensuring that the formulations are highly efficient and reliable. With BELSIL®, you can tailor your hair-care or skin-care formulations or color cosmetics to obtain end products that are not only competitive but also meet the needs of the market.

data.name: CAVACURMIN
data.description: CAVACURMIN® is a highly bioavailable curcumin complex that is around 40 times more efficiently absorbed than standard turmeric extract. The complexation with the naturally occurring oligasaccharide gamma-cyclodextrin results in a free-flowing, easily dispersible powder.

data.name: BELSIL® PF 100
data.description: BELSIL® PF 100 is an aryl- and alkyl-modified silicone fluid of medium viscosity. BELSIL® PF 100 is characterized by having a higher refractive index than standard dimethicone fluids (1.38-1.40). It offers significant improvements in regards to gloss and shine. BELSIL® PF 100 is used in all kinds of cosmetic formulations, but mostly in hair care compositions and color cosmetics due to its shine-enhancing benefits.

data.name: HDK® H20

summary.name: Certifications & Compliance
items: Comprehensive Environmental Response, Compensations & Liability Act (CERCLA)

data.description: HDK® H20 is a synthetic, hydrophobic, amorphous silica produced via flame hydrolysis. It is a white colloidal powder of high purity. HDK® H20 is used as a thickening and thixotropic agent in coatings, printing inks, adhesives, cosmetics, and other applications. It also serves as a reinforcing filler in elastomers, particularly silicone-elastomers. Additionally, HDK® H20 acts as a free flow additive in the production of powder coatings.

data.name: DEHESIVE® EM 492
data.description: DEHESIVE® EM 492 is an emulsion-containing polymer used in combination with WACKER® Emulsion crosslinkers and catalysts. The product is designed for addition-curing coating applications, with a focus on the production of release papers and temperature-sensitive films on converting machines. It also exhibits excellent anchorage to a wide variety of substrates.

data.name: VINNAPAS® SAF 34
data.description: VINNAPAS® SAF 34 is a fine-particle dispersion of a special styrene/acrylate copolymer. It is produced without the use of alkyl phenol ethoxylate (APEO)-containing compounds. VINNAPAS® SAF 34 exhibits excellent pigment binding properties, great adhesion to inorganic substrates, very good water resistance, excellent alkali resistance, very low dirt pick-up, and great versatility.

data.name: HDK® N20Plus
data.description: HDK® N20Plus is a hydrophilic, synthetic, amorphous silica produced through flame hydrolysis. It is a standard product widely used in various industrial applications. HDK® N20Plus is a white colloidal powder of high purity. It finds applications in offset printing and powder coatings.

data.name: ELASTOSIL® LR 3040/60 A/B
data.description: ELASTOSIL® LR 3040/60 A/B is a liquid silicone rubber from the ELASTOSIL® LR 3040 series. It is a paste-like, easily pigmentable, two-component compound with a very short curing time. The vulcanizates of this product are renowned for their high transparency as well as their exceptional mechanical and electrical properties. They are particularly noted for their high tear resistance according to DIN ISO 34-1 A (trousers) and ASTM D 624 B (crescent).

data.name: LIOSIL® eco F 100
data.description: LIOSIL eco F 100 is a linear, non-reactive, unmodified polydimethylsiloxane with a viscosity of approximately 100 mm²/s. In its manufacturing process, LIOSIL® eco F 100 replaces 100% of fossil-based raw materials with renewable raw materials (biomethanol) using a REDcert² biomass balance approach audited by TÜV NORD. Thanks to its unique chemical structure, LIOSIL® eco F 100 offers exceptional properties that distinguish it from organic materials like mineral oils. Notably, it exhibits a low surface tension and excellent spreading properties.

data.name: ELASTOSIL® N199 Transparent
data.description: ELASTOSIL N199 TRANSPARENT is a non-slump, neutral-cure silicone sealant that cures at room temperature under the influence of atmospheric moisture. ELASTOSIL® N199 Transparent exhibits excellent primerless adhesion to many substrates with high tear strength. It is a multipurpose adhesive and sealant for the electronics industry, with typical uses for CIPG- and FIPG-applications.

data.name: VINNAPAS® EZ 222
data.description: VINNAPAS® EZ 222 is a vinyl acetate-ethylene (VAE) copolymer dispersion stabilized with hydroxyethyl cellulose and surfactant. It has a glass transition temperature (Tg) of +18.0°C. This dispersion offers excellent scrub resistance, good flow and leveling properties, and low viscosity. It has a high solid content and is produced without the use of APEOs.

content_blocks.html:
The SILRES® brand comprises a long-established, yet innovative portfolio that provides
buildings and surfaces with long-lasting protection against water damage. It is highly effective on both mineral materials and wood.

Effects:

  • Low water uptake
  • High water-vapor permeability
  • Barrier against harmful, water-soluble salts
  • High resistance to heat, cold and UV light

Applications:

  • Binders and additives for durable decorative coatings
  • Silane/siloxane creams, emulsions and liquids for protecting concrete
  • Impregnation agents for hydrophobic impregnation of facades
  • Silicone emulsions for hydrophobic impregnation of insulation materials
  • Silicones for hydrophobic impregnation of brick and roof tiles
  • Water-repellent additives for producing gypsum-based materials
  • Silicone powders as water-repellent additives for dry-mixes
  • Water-repellent additives for cement-fiber boards and similar materials
  • Silicone microemulsion concentrate and cream for horizontal damp-proofing
  • Hydrophobic impregnation agents and additives for wood
  • Surface treatment of mineral substrates with anti-stain, color-enhancing and anti-graffiti effects

For industrial coatings, the SILRES® brand offers highly crosslinked polysiloxanes that have organic side groups and are available as resins and intermediates. This combination of organic groups and an inorganic backbone confers exceptional properties.

Effects:

  • Protection against extreme heat and rapid temperature changes
  • Excellent resistance to UV and weathering
  • Versatile styling combined with high functionality

 

Applications:

SILRES® silicone resins make ideal binders for:

  • Heat-resistant coatings for exhaust and engine parts
  • Heat-resistant exterior paints in the chemical and petrochemical industries
  • Decorative and functional coatings for stoves, fireplaces and barbecues
  • Weatherable topcoats, e.g. for high-performance steel structures, such as bridges or buildings and offshore platforms in highly corrosive environments

SILRES® intermediates greatly enhance the heat and weathering resistance of organic binders. The resulting optimized coatings are used for:

  • Weatherable coil-coating finishes, e.g. for roofing
  • Heat-resistant decorative coatings for pots and pans and kitchen appliances such as toasters, waffle irons, etc.

data.name: SILRES® 604
data.description: SILRES® 604 is a flaked silicone resin that exhibits good compatibility with organic resins. It is primarily used as a pure binder in various applications. It is supplied as a solvent-free solid resin. One of the key applications of SILRES® 604 is as a base material for powder coatings. It is particularly suitable for heat-resistant formulations that can withstand temperatures up to 650 °C. Furthermore, when used in white formulations, SILRES® 604 can maintain its color stability up to temperatures as high as 270 °C without significant yellowing. The ability of SILRES® 604 to act as a pure binder and its high-temperature resistance make it a valuable component in the formulation of heat-resistant powder coatings.

data.name: SILRES® 610
data.description: SILRES® 610 is a hard, solid silicone resin containing methyl groups. It is supplied in the form of solid flakes. A typical application is its use as a binder for high-temperature-resistant coatings after being dissolved in a suitable solvent. SILRES® 610 is utilized as a binder in coatings, offering a combination of heat resistance and weathering resistance. Additionally, it dries quickly, resulting in a film that is free from tackiness.

data.name: SILRES® 64558 VP
data.description: SILRES® 64558 VP is a toluene-based, ready-to-use formulation based on polysiloxanes and silicone resins. The product is preferably used as a binder in highly flexible composite tapes or as an intermediate to manufacture silicone pressure-sensitive adhesive (PSA) formulations. In composite tapes, SILRES® 64558 VP contributes to the tapes' excellent electrical insulation properties and outstanding long-term heat resistance. Besides, composite tapes made with SILRES® 64558 VP are highly stable against environmental impacts such as moisture, pollutants, and UV light, allowing them to be exposed continuously to constantly changing climatic conditions or UV radiation.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1001
data.description: SILRES® BS 1001 is a water-thinnable, solventless emulsion based on a mixture of silane and siloxane. Dilute solutions of SILRES® BS 1001 serve as high-quality, general-purpose water repellents for impregnating and priming mineral surfaces. SILRES® BS 1001 can be combined with polymer-based primers for substrate consolidation.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1001 A
data.description: SILRES® BS 1001 A is a stable, VOC-compliant, 50% active silicone emulsion that reduces with water to form a stable, penetrating water repellent emulsion. SILRES® BS 1001 A is developed to treat a wide variety of mineral substrates, including architectural concrete, concrete block, split-face block, pavers, stucco, porous and dense brick, clay tile, and exposed aggregate concrete. It is particularly effective in the do-it-yourself (DIY) markets, where good water repellency, beading, ease of use, and stability are required. SILRES® BS 1001 A is not recommended for below-grade applications where hydrostatic pressure can be significant.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1042
data.description: SILRES® BS 1042 is an aqueous emulsion of a reactive polydimethylsiloxane. Its purpose is to provide water repellency to materials such as glass wool mats or rock wool mats that are bound with phenolic resin. It can also be used for low-density bulk goods like perlite or vermiculite. The emulsion helps to impart water-repellent properties to these materials, enhancing their performance in moisture-related applications.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1052
data.description: SILRES® BS 1052 is an aqueous and water-dilutable emulsion of a medium-viscosity polydimethylsiloxane. Its main purpose is to provide water repellency to materials such as glass wool (fiberglass) or stone wool. It can be used on both bound materials, where the wool is bound with a resin, as well as unbound materials without a resin. By applying SILRES® BS 1052, it helps to enhance the water-repellent properties of these materials, improving their performance in moisture-related applications.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1306
data.description: SILRES® BS 1306 is a solventless, water-thinnable emulsion of polysiloxane modified with functional silicone resin. It can also be used as a water-repellent primer, in which case it should be diluted with water at a ratio of 1 part SILRES® BS 1306 to 9 parts water. If the primer is required to strengthen the substrate, we recommend adding a polymer dispersion in hydrosol form.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1310
data.description: SILRES® BS 1310 is a solvent-free, water-thinnable emulsion of polysiloxane modified with functional silicone resin. It is an additive used in the production of aqueous masonry coatings and aqueous primers to enhance water repellency and resistance. Additionally, it improves the processability and antiblocking characteristics of the aqueous coatings.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1316
data.description: SILRES® BS 1316 is used undiluted as a water-repellent primer and impregnating agent for normal and reinforced concrete. It is a mixture of isomeric octyltrimethoxysilanes, with isooctyltrimethoxysilane as the main component. SILRES® BS 1316 is specifically recommended as a water-repellent impregnating agent and primer for normal and reinforced concrete in various applications such as bridges, roads, and buildings.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1340
data.description: SILRES® BS 1340 is a nonionic, solvent-free, waterborne emulsion of a reactive polysiloxane. It is specifically used in the formulation of water-resistant coatings. SILRES® BS 1340 can be directly incorporated, without dilution, into waterborne masonry paints and plasters either during or after their production.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1346
data.description: SILRES® BS 1346 is a nonionic, solvent-free, water-dilutable emulsion of a reactive polysiloxane. It is used in its undiluted form as a hydrophobizing additive for aqueous masonry paints or plasters. Its purpose is to increase water repellency, water resistance, and water vapor permeability while also enhancing processability and antiblocking properties.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1360
data.description: SILRES® BS 1360 is a nonionic, solvent-free, water-dilutable emulsion of a reactive polysiloxane. It can be added in undiluted form to aqueous masonry protection agents either during or after their production. Similar to SILRES® BS 1346, SILRES® BS 1360 is used undiluted as a hydrophobizing additive for aqueous masonry paints. Its primary functions are to enhance water repellency, water resistance, water vapor permeability, processability, and anti-blocking properties.

data.name: SILRES® BS 16
data.description: SILRES® BS 16 is an aqueous solution of potassium methyl siliconate used in diluted form for the hydrophobic impregnation of mineral construction materials, making them water-repellent. The water-repellent properties of SILRES® BS 16 are developed through its reaction with atmospheric carbon dioxide (CO2), forming polymethylsilicic acid. However, it should be noted that, like all siliconates, SILRES® BS 16 may cause a white deposit on the surface of colored construction materials if used outside the recommended application guidelines.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1601
data.description: SILRES® BS 1601 is n-octyltriethoxysilane, which is used undiluted as a water-repellent primer and impregnating agent for normal and reinforced concrete. It offers significant benefits such as the reduction of chloride and water absorption by the concrete, minimizing concrete loss due to freeze/road salt attack, and exhibiting low volatility. Once applied to the concrete, SILRES® BS 1601 reacts with atmospheric moisture or pore water present in the concrete, resulting in the generation of the active ingredient. This active ingredient effectively reduces the water absorbency of the treated concrete while maintaining a high level of water vapor permeability. Importantly, the treatment does not block pores or capillaries within the concrete.

data.name: SILRES® BS 16040
data.description: SILRES® BS 16040 is a water-dilutable, solvent-free silane emulsion. It is a high-quality specialty product used for the hydrophobic impregnation and priming of alkaline substrates. When applied to construction materials, SILRES® BS 16040 reacts with atmospheric moisture and/or water present in the pores of the building material. This reaction eliminates alcohol and forms an active substance that greatly reduces the absorbency of the concrete within the active zone (penetration depth after post-treatment). Importantly, this reduction in absorbency occurs without blocking any pores or capillaries in the material. As a result of the impregnation, the treated building material retains its high water-vapor permeability, allowing moisture to pass through while still providing excellent protection against water penetration.

data.name: SILRES® BS 168
data.description: SILRES® BS 168 is a water-based, solvent-free, and silicone-based pH adjuster that is specifically used in waterborne emulsion paints. It serves the purpose of improving pH adjustment and wet abrasion resistance in paint formulations. This product is particularly suitable for formulating low VOC (volatile organic compound) and low odor paints, meeting the requirements for environmentally friendly and sustainable coating solutions. By using SILRES® BS 168, paint manufacturers can achieve effective pH adjustment while maintaining excellent wet abrasion resistance properties.

data.name: SILRES® BS 17
data.description: SILRES® BS 17 is a solventless concentrate that is based on silanes and siloxanes. It is specifically used in water-diluted form for the hydrophobation (waterproofing) of silicate-based mineral construction materials that are produced in plants. One of the key advantages of SILRES® BS 17 is that it is a water-free and solventless silicone concentrate. It can be easily diluted with drinking water without the need for sophisticated mixing devices. This allows for convenient and efficient dilution, making the application process simpler for users.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1701
data.description: SILRES® BS 1701 is a mixture of octyltriethoxysilane isomers, with iso-octyltriethoxysilane as the main component. It is used undiluted for the hydrophobic priming and impregnation of concrete and reinforced concrete. Additionally, SILRES® BS 1701 is suitable for the hydrophobic treatment of fillers and pigments.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1702
data.description: SILRES® BS 1702 is a solvent-free mixture of silane and siloxane that can be applied either in undiluted form or diluted with organic solvents. It is specifically designed as a high-quality specialty water repellent for impregnating fiber cement. When applied to fiber cement, SILRES® BS 1702 acts as an effective water repellent, helping to protect the material from moisture absorption and potential damage caused by water.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1703 SQ (000010587)
data.description: SILRES® BS 1703 SQ (000010587) is specifically designed for the in-plant water-repellent treatment of fiber-reinforced cement products, including fiber-cement boards. Its main purpose is to greatly reduce the capillary water absorption of these construction materials once they have set and reached equilibrium moisture. The use of SILRES® BS 1703 SQ provides enhanced protection against water damage, contributing to the longevity and quality of fiber-reinforced cement products.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1703 SQ (000096394)
data.description: SILRES® BS 1703 SQ (000096394) is also primarily intended for in-plant water-repellent treatment of fiber-reinforced cement products, such as fiber-cement boards. It exhibits a higher flash point and increased storage stability compared to SILRES® BS 1703. While it may have a slightly opalescent appearance with a slight yellowish discoloration, it does not affect the excellent performance of the product.

data.name: SILRES® BS 17040
data.description: SILRES® BS 17040 is a high-quality, water-thinnable silane emulsion that is solvent-free. It is specifically formulated to act as a water repellent for impregnating and priming alkaline mineral surfaces. Additionally, it can be used as a water-resisting admixture for non-load-bearing manufactured concrete products.

data.name: SILRES® BS 17040 A
data.description: SILRES® BS 17040 A is a water-thinnable, solventless silane emulsion that serves as a high-quality water repellent for impregnating and priming alkaline mineral surfaces. Similar to SILRES® BS 17040, it can be used as a water-resisting admixture for non-load-bearing manufactured concrete products.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1705
data.description: SILRES® BS 1705 is a high-quality water-thinnable emulsion that is solvent-free and based on a mixture of silane and siloxane compounds. It is specifically designed to act as a specialty water repellent for impregnating cement-based products, including fiber cement. By impregnating cement-based materials, such as fiber cement, with SILRES® BS 1705, their water repellency is significantly enhanced, providing long-lasting protection against water absorption and related problems. This makes SILRES® BS 1705 an excellent choice for improving the durability and performance of cement-based products in various applications.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1801
data.description: SILRES® BS 1801 is a mixture of octyltriethoxysilane isomers, with iso-octyltriethoxysilane as the main component. It is used in its undiluted form as an admixture for the integral waterproofing of fresh concrete. SILRES® BS 1801 is highly recommended as a concrete waterproofing admixture.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1802
data.description: SILRES® BS 1802 is an admixture for the integral waterproofing of fresh concrete in its undiluted form. Additionally, it can be utilized as a water-resisting admixture for non-load-bearing manufactured concrete products. SILRES® BS 1802 effectively prolongs the service life of concrete structures by inhibiting the alkali-silica reaction (ASR).

data.name: SILRES® BS 1803
data.description: SILRES® BS 1803 is a solvent-free emulsion based on organo-modified silanes and siloxanes. It is specifically designed to act as a water-repellent admixture for semi-dry concrete and other non-load-bearing cement-based building materials, including paving stones and concrete blocks. SILRES® BS 1803 helps to minimize the amount of water absorbed by the concrete or other cement-based materials, thereby enhancing their durability and resistance to moisture-related issues.

data.name: SILRES® BS 1803 A
data.description: SILRES® BS 1803 A is a stable and VOC-compliant silicone emulsion with a 60% active content. It is specifically designed to reduce water uptake and create visual beading on concrete substrates while allowing the pores and capillaries to remain unblocked. This product is particularly effective when it comes to preventing water uptake and promoting beads, even at very low addition levels. One of the main applications of SILRES® BS 1803 A is as an admixture for non-load bearing cement-based formulated products, including precast products, blocks, and pavers. By incorporating this emulsion into the formulation, the resulting products gain enhanced waterproofing properties and resistance to water penetration. Furthermore, SILRES® BS 1803 A can also be used as a topical sealer for post-treatment of cement-based formulated products.

data.name: SILRES® BS 2001
data.description: SILRES® BS 2001 is a water-thinnable, solventless emulsion based on a mixture of silane and siloxane. It is a ready-to-use solution that serves as a high-quality water repellent for impregnating and priming mineral surfaces. After application, the emulsion undergoes hydrolysis, releasing alcohol and converting into a silicone resin.

data.name: SILRES® BS 2410 A
data.description: SILRES® BS 2410 A is a highly active, functional epoxy silicone macro-emulsion. It is designed for use in the hydrophobation of paper backing for gypsum board. It is particularly suitable for permeating through paper backer fibers without affecting the adhesion properties of gypsum. It does not cause shade change and has no concerns about the yellowing effect.

data.name: SILRES® BS 280
data.description: SILRES® BS 280 is a solvent-free silicone concentrate based on silane or siloxane. It can be diluted with organic solvents. Diluted solutions of SILRES® BS 280 are high-quality water repellents for impregnating mineral building materials, especially silicate-free natural stones like limestone or gypsum. The water-repellent effect develops after application through a reaction with atmospheric humidity.

data.name: SILRES® BS 280 CF
data.description: SILRES® BS 280 CF is a solvent-free silicone concentrate based on silane or siloxane. Like SILRES® BS 280, it can be diluted with organic solvents. Diluted solutions of SILRES® BS 280 CF serve as high-quality water repellents for impregnating mineral building materials, particularly silicate-free natural stones like limestone or gypsum. It also develops its water-repellent effect through a reaction with atmospheric humidity.

data.name: SILRES® BS 290
data.description: SILRES® BS 290 is a solventless silicone concentrate based on a mixture of silane and siloxane. It can be diluted with organic solvents. Dilute solutions of SILRES® BS 290 in organic solvents are high-quality general-purpose water repellents for impregnating and priming mineral and highly alkaline substrates.

data.name: SILRES® BS 290 CF
data.description: SILRES® BS 290 CF is a solventless silicone concentrate based on a mixture of silane and siloxane. Like SILRES® BS 290, it can be diluted with organic solvents. Dilute solutions of SILRES® BS 290 CF in organic solvents serve as high-quality general-purpose water repellents for impregnating and priming mineral and highly alkaline substrates.

data.name: SILRES® 603
data.description: SILRES® 603 is a solid silicone resin that contains phenyl groups and is known for its good compatibility with organic polymers. It serves as a base material for heat-resistant powder coatings, particularly those that require above-average gloss retention during heating. When creating heat-resistant and black pigmented powder coatings, it is recommended to blend SILRES® 603 with organic binders specifically designed for powder coatings. Additionally, the inclusion of heat-resistant pigments can further enhance its performance.
